<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-52-0201 </DOCNO><TEXT>The effects of sulfur dioxide on plants are described, along with theenvironmental factors that affect susceptibility and the species differencesin susceptibility. The characteristic injuries caused by sulfur dioxideare described. Similar treatment is given hydrofluoric acid, chlorine,hydrogen sulfide, ammonia, and mercury vapor. A brief discussion alongthe same lines is presented for ethylene and carbon monoxide. 23 references,3 figures.</TEXT></DOC>